.DT
exit_command
$MUDNAME$ Creator Help
exit_command

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
exit_command -  This method is called whenever someone enters a command.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
varargs int exit_command(string word,
mixed verb,
object thing)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^word%^RESET%^ - the command entered
%^BOLD%^verb%^RESET%^ - no idea
%^BOLD%^thing%^RESET%^ - the object moving, not really used
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
1 if the command matched an exit and the move
was successful, 0 if not

.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/living/living.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method is called whenever someone enters a command.
It is here that the exits of the room are checked to see
if the command entered is a move command.
.EP

